window.containerItems().find and bot.clickWindow are not working after change pages in this code: let page = itemData[itemname][0]
for (i = 0; i < page - 1; i++) {
bot.on("windowOpen", async function ChangePageGui(window) {
bot.clickWindow(53, 0, 0)
bot.removeListener("windowOpen", ChangePageGui)
})
}

let index = itemData[itemname][1] - 1
bot.on("windowOpen", async function ClickItemGui(window) {
bot.clickWindow(index, 0, 0)
bot.removeListener("windowOpen", ClickItemGui)
})

It appears you may be using functions before the windowOpen event is emitted. You should wrap your bot.clickWindow and bot.removeListener functions inside the event listener functions to make sure they are executed only after the browser windows open.

Try updating your code to this:

```javascript
let page = itemData[itemname][0]
for (i = 0; i < page - 1; i++) {
  bot.once("windowOpen", async function ChangePageGui(window) {
    await bot.clickWindow(53, 0, 0)
  })
}

let index = itemData[itemname][1] - 1
bot.once("windowOpen", async function ClickItemGui(window) {
  await bot.clickWindow(index, 0, 0)
})
```

I made these changes:

1. Move bot.clickWindow and bot.removeListener inside the corresponding event listeners.
2. Use "once" instead of "on" to automatically remove the event listener after it's triggered.
3. Use "await" to ensure bot.clickWindow action is executed before proceeding.

Please check if this solves your issue. If not, additional information and code may be necessary to understand the root cause.

